if I put my confidence in gold,

00:47:22.219 --> 00:47:25.219
Job was wealthy at the start,

00:47:25.219 --> 00:47:28.219
but he was not greedily materialistic.

00:47:28.219 --> 00:47:31.219
And when he lost all his wealth,

00:47:31.219 --> 00:47:33.219
he accepted the fact that as he said,

00:47:33.219 --> 00:47:35.219
naked he came out of his mother's womb

00:47:35.219 --> 00:47:38.219
and naked he would return.

00:47:38.219 --> 00:47:40.219
So people of integrity did not put their trust

00:47:40.219 --> 00:47:42.219
in material things.

00:47:42.219 --> 00:47:45.219
They put the kingdom first in their life.

00:47:45.219 --> 00:47:47.219
One more example, verse 33,

00:47:47.219 --> 00:47:50.219
he said, have I ever tried to cover

00:47:50.219 --> 00:47:53.219
over my transgressions?

00:47:53.219 --> 00:47:57.219
In Job 1323, Job asked for his sins

00:47:57.219 --> 00:48:00.219
and transgressions to be revealed.

00:48:00.219 --> 00:48:03.219
And in the end, he accepted reproof

00:48:03.219 --> 00:48:07.219
for his being too quick to declare himself righteous.

00:48:07.219 --> 00:48:11.219
And after Elihu and Jehovah both chasing Job,

00:48:11.219 --> 00:48:14.219
he repented in dust and ashes.

00:48:14.219 --> 00:48:16.219
So people of integrity are quick

00:48:16.219 --> 00:48:18.219
to own up to their own mistakes

00:48:18.219 --> 00:48:21.219
and accept correction.

00:48:21.219 --> 00:48:24.219
Surely Job was a model of integrity.

00:48:24.219 --> 00:48:26.219
Did you know that he requested

00:48:26.219 --> 00:48:28.219
that a written record be made

00:48:28.219 --> 00:48:31.219
of his suffering and endurance?

00:48:31.219 --> 00:48:34.219
He did, if you turn to Job chapter 19,

00:48:34.219 --> 00:48:39.219
Job 19, starting with verse 23,

00:48:39.219 --> 00:48:44.630
he said, if only my words were written down,

00:48:44.630 --> 00:48:47.630
if only they could be inscribed in a book,

00:48:47.630 --> 00:48:50.630
or that they were carved forever in the rock

00:48:50.630 --> 00:48:54.630
with an iron stylus and lead.

00:48:54.630 --> 00:48:56.630
How thankful we are that Jehovah agreed

00:48:56.630 --> 00:48:59.630
to make a permanent record of Job's integrity

00:48:59.630 --> 00:49:02.630
keeping course and that he put it in the Bible

00:49:02.630 --> 00:49:04.630
and did not have it cherished,

00:49:04.630 --> 00:49:06.630
chiseled on some rock

00:49:06.630 --> 00:49:09.630
in the middle of Arabia where Job lived.

00:49:10.630 --> 00:49:14.630
Can you sum up the story of Job in one sentence?

00:49:14.630 --> 00:49:19.630
Well, one Bible commentary does quite well by stating,

00:49:19.630 --> 00:49:21.630
the beauty of the book of Job is

00:49:21.630 --> 00:49:24.630
of a living, breathing soul,

00:49:24.630 --> 00:49:26.630
encompassed by sorrows,

00:49:26.630 --> 00:49:28.630
surrounded by misunderstanding,

00:49:28.630 --> 00:49:31.630
but unconquered, humbled,

00:49:31.630 --> 00:49:35.630
and finally, satisfied in God.

00:49:35.630 --> 00:49:37.630
Through Job's life, we learn

00:49:37.630 --> 00:49:40.630
that no matter what trials we may encounter,

00:49:40.630 --> 00:49:42.630
having a close relationship with Jehovah

00:49:42.630 --> 00:49:46.630
