it's time for our postcard.

00:54:22.400 --> 00:54:24.400
When you envision a paradise,

00:54:24.400 --> 00:54:27.400
you may think of pristine beaches,

00:54:27.400 --> 00:54:29.400
swaying palm trees,

00:54:29.400 --> 00:54:30.400
rainforests,

00:54:30.400 --> 00:54:33.400
and coral reefs teeming with life.

00:54:33.400 --> 00:54:36.400
You may picture Samoa.

00:54:36.400 --> 00:54:39.400
The Samoa and islands sparkle like gems

00:54:39.400 --> 00:54:42.400
in the South Pacific Ocean.

00:54:42.400 --> 00:54:44.400
The islands are divided into two parts,

00:54:44.400 --> 00:54:47.400
Samoa and American Samoa.

00:54:47.400 --> 00:54:50.400
Although separated by only about 65 kilometers

00:54:50.400 --> 00:54:52.400
or about 40 miles,

00:54:52.400 --> 00:54:54.400
they lie on either side

00:54:54.400 --> 00:54:56.400
of the international date line,

00:54:56.400 --> 00:54:59.400
creating a time difference of a full day.

00:54:59.400 --> 00:55:01.400
This means that each year,

00:55:01.400 --> 00:55:04.400
one of the first memorial talks is given in Samoa,

00:55:04.400 --> 00:55:09.400
while one of the last is held in American Samoa.

00:55:09.400 --> 00:55:12.400
The coconut tree is abundant here.

00:55:13.400 --> 00:55:16.400
Samoans call it the tree of life,

00:55:16.400 --> 00:55:18.400
because it can be used for food,

00:55:18.400 --> 00:55:20.400
drink, medicine,

00:55:20.400 --> 00:55:22.400
fuel, and shelter.

00:55:22.400 --> 00:55:24.400
In 1940,

00:55:24.400 --> 00:55:27.400
Harold Gill visited the Samoan islands to preach,

00:55:27.400 --> 00:55:30.400
but was promptly asked to leave.

00:55:30.400 --> 00:55:33.400
In the five days before the next boat sailed,

00:55:33.400 --> 00:55:37.400
he distributed literature far and wide by bicycle.

00:55:37.400 --> 00:55:40.400
One booklet found its way to Pele Foyopolo.

00:55:40.400 --> 00:55:43.400
12 years later, in 1952,

00:55:43.400 --> 00:55:46.400
after Pele met a brother from England at work,

00:55:46.400 --> 00:55:48.400
he and his wife, Ilua,

00:55:48.400 --> 00:55:52.400
became the first Samoans to be baptized.

00:55:52.400 --> 00:55:54.400
Today, there are 12 congregations

00:55:54.400 --> 00:55:58.400
with 606 publishers in Samoa.

00:55:58.400 --> 00:56:01.400
Brothers at the remote translation office

00:56:01.400 --> 00:56:03.400
on the island of Upolu

00:56:03.400 --> 00:56:06.400
translate publications into Samoan.

00:56:06.400 --> 00:56:08.400
Witnesses can be found preaching and appear.

00:56:08.400 --> 00:56:10.400
Samoans main port,

00:56:10.400 --> 00:56:14.400
but most Samoans live in rural coastal areas.

00:56:14.400 --> 00:56:17.400
So our brothers witness in villages,

00:56:17.400 --> 00:56:18.400
tarot plantations,

00:56:18.400 --> 00:56:20.400
and the remote island of Manono,

00:56:20.400 --> 00:56:23.400
reachable only by boat.

00:56:23.400 --> 00:56:25.400
With no cars on Manono,

00:56:25.400 --> 00:56:30.400
publishers walk the island in search of interested ones.

00:56:30.400 --> 00:56:33.400
When our brothers get together for association,

00:56:33.400 --> 00:56:35.400
they enjoy delicious foods,

00:56:35.400 --> 00:56:36.400
including tarot,

00:56:36.400 --> 00:56:37.400
breadfruit,

00:56:37.400 --> 00:56:38.400
coconut milk,

00:56:38.400 --> 00:56:39.400
oka,

00:56:39.400 --> 00:56:41.400
which is raw fish in coconut cream,

00:56:41.400 --> 00:56:44.400
and their famous hot chocolate,

00:56:44.400 --> 00:56:47.400
Koko Samoa.

00:56:47.400 --> 00:56:48.400
On Sundays,

00:56:48.400 --> 00:56:50.400
families spend hours together

00:56:50.400 --> 00:56:52.400
enjoying a feast of foods

00:56:52.400 --> 00:56:54.400
cooked in a traditional umu.

00:56:54.400 --> 00:56:58.400
An above ground oven made of volcanic rock.

00:56:58.400 --> 00:56:59.400
They enjoy music,

00:56:59.400 --> 00:57:00.400
singing,

00:57:00.400 --> 00:57:02.400
and traditional dancing.

00:57:02.400 --> 00:57:03.400
The Siva,

00:57:03.400 --> 00:57:04.400
and Fatalpati,

00:57:04.400 --> 00:57:06.400
or slap dance.

00:57:07.400 --> 00:57:09.400
The Salihapaga congregation

00:57:09.400 --> 00:57:12.400
is on the island of Uppolo.

00:57:12.400 --> 00:57:14.400
Its territory includes beaches,

00:57:14.400 --> 00:57:16.400
and the Tohswa Ocean Trench,

00:57:16.400 --> 00:57:20.400
a volcanic swimming hole popular with tourists.

00:57:20.400 --> 00:57:22.400
The 21 publishers,

00:57:22.400 --> 00:57:24.400
of the Salihapaga congregation,

00:57:24.400 --> 00:57:28.400
send their warm love and greetings.

